sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K676013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A device to detects the level of stress due to a GBS being present on the plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Meng Li

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K239009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP test devise for Spy promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Hopefully the spy promoter can be used to detect presence of relevant unfolded proteins in the periplasmic space, to detect shear stress or other so far undefined relevant stress.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xiang Chen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K676001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Gyrase Binding Site from Mu Bacteriophage
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The strong gyrase site clones from Mu bacteriophage.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Meng Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Cloned it from the bacteriophage genome by PCR using synthesised primers.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K239001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Spy promoter, activated by Phosporylated CpxR, BaeR and Sigma70
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence contains 2 phosphorylated BaeR binding sites, 1 phosphorylated CpxR binding site and transcription is initiated by sigma factor 70. Function: Can detect various periplasmic stresses. Area of application: Hopefully it can be used to detect presence of relevant unfolded proteins in the periplasmic space, to detect shear stress or other so far undefined relevant stress.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Axel Nystrom
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequence from biocyc, Escherichia coli K-12. Native unmodified sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Detect and remove possible restriction sites: XbaI, EcoRI, PstI, SpeI, AgeI, BamHI, BglII, NogMIV, NotI and XhoI. No restriction site had to be removed. Sequence starts 3 bp before the first BaeR binding site and ends 5 pb after the -10 box.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: green fluorescent protein derived from jellyfish Aequeora victoria wild-type GFP (SwissProt: P42212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: GFP (mut3b) [note that this part does not have a barcode]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
